abstract: The former R.E.M. frontman shares the titles he’d bring with him on a desert island.
snippet: The former R.E.M. frontman shares the titles he’d bring with him on a desert island.
lead_paragraph: For his new bookshop installation, One Grand, the editor Aaron Hicklin asked people to name the 10 books they’d take with them if they were marooned on a desert island. The next installment in the series comes from Michael Stipe, the artist and former frontman of the band R.E.M., who shares his picks exclusively with T.

abstract: Kerry Ryan was 21 and had just arrived from Ireland when she replied to 43-year-old John Juback’s classified ad in The Village Voice. It has been 24 years since she came to check out the place.
snippet: Kerry Ryan was 21 and had just arrived from Ireland when she replied to 43-year-old John Juback’s classified ad in The Village Voice. It has been 24 years since she came to check out the place.
lead_paragraph: Kerry Ryan needed a new place to live; her crazy Yugoslavian roommate had become unbearable. So, as people did in 1991 in New York City, she turned to the classified ads in The Village Voice.

abstract: A critical guide to productions in New York City, including shows in previews.
snippet: A critical guide to productions in New York City, including shows in previews.
lead_paragraph: Approximate running times are in parentheses. Theaters are in Manhattan unless otherwise noted. Full reviews of current productions, additional listings, showtimes and ticket information are at nytimes.com/theater. A searchable, critical guide to theater is at nytimes.com/events.

abstract: A critical guide to productions in New York City, including shows in previews.
snippet: A critical guide to productions in New York City, including shows in previews.
lead_paragraph: Approximate running times are in parentheses. Theaters are in Manhattan unless otherwise noted. Full reviews of current productions, additional listings, showtimes and ticket information are at nytimes.com/theater. A searchable, critical guide to theater is at nytimes.com/events.

abstract: The idea put forward by the House is that an overhaul of the international business tax code would produce money to pay for a long-term bill.
snippet: The idea put forward by the House is that an overhaul of the international business tax code would produce money to pay for a long-term bill.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — More than 30 times over the past six years, Congress has mustered the money only for short-term extensions of the federal highway trust fund, the equivalent of repeatedly putting $5 of gas in an empty tank.
